1. Scheduler Implementation
Create a scheduler in the push-notification service.
Scheduler should periodically fetch records with push status = P (Pending).
2. Fetch Required Data
Use existing queries in push-notification service to retrieve:
orderInfo
paymentInfo
merchantUrl
3. Request Preparation
Create a request object containing:
Order information
Payment information
Merchant URL
Convert the request object into JSON string format before publishing.
4. Merchant Type Verification
Call admin-service to fetch merchantInfo.
Determine whether the merchant is:
Custom Merchant
Standard Merchant
5. Kafka Publishing
If merchant type = Custom Merchant
Publish the prepared request payload to Kafka topic.
If merchant type = Standard Merchant
Skip publishing.
6. Push Status Update
After successful Kafka publish:
Update push notification status from
P → IN (In Progress).
Acceptance Criteria
Scheduler should trigger and process push notifications with status = P.
System should fetch orderInfo, paymentInfo, and merchantUrl correctly.
System should call admin-service to determine merchant type.
Kafka message should be published only for custom merchants.
Kafka message payload should be in JSON string format.
Push notification status should update from P to IN after successful publish.
If merchant is standard, no message should be published.
Proper logging should be added for:
Scheduler execution
Admin-service response
Kafka publish success/failure
Status update.
